<para style="p">For the chief musician; set to Mahalath. A maschil of David.</para>

<para style="b" />

<para style="q1">

<verse number="1" style="v" />A fool says in his heart, "There is no God."</para>

<para style="q1">They are corrupt and have done abominable iniquity;</para>

<para style="q1">there is no one who does good.</para>

<para style="q1">

<verse number="2" style="v" />God looks down from heaven on the children of mankind</para>

<para style="q1">to see if there are any who understand,</para>

<para style="q1">who seek after him.</para>

<para style="q1">

<verse number="3" style="v" />They have all turned away. Together they have become corrupt.</para>

<para style="q1">There is not one who does good, not even one.</para>
